{"vegetarian": true, "glutenFree": true, "title": "Baked Chickpea and Chili Koftas in a Hot Jalfrezi Curry Sauce", "veryPopular": false, "gaps": "no", "sourceUrl": "http://www.foodista.com/recipe/TDJKCX7Y/baked-chickpea-chili-koftas-in-a-hot-jalfrezi-curry-sauce", "sourceName": "Foodista", "vegan": true, "sustainable": false, "instructions": "<ol><li>Preheat oven to 180 degrees celcius (356 Fahrenheit) and line a large baking tray with parchment paper.</li><li>Make the Kofta  Heat 2 tbsp water in a saute pan over a medium heat and add the onion, garlic and chili and cook for 4 minutes, transfer to a food processor (or use a stick blender) add the coriander and the Kofta Spice Mix and pulse until smooth.</li><li>In a large mixing bowl, mash the chickpeas until they are all crushed then add the mixture from step 2 along with the gram flour and mix thoroughly together, if its too wet, add a little more gram flour. Using damp hands take a heaped tablespoon of the kofta mixture and shape into a ball and place on the parchment paper, you should get 18  20 koftas. Cook in the oven for 20  25 minutes, they should firm up quite nicely in the oven.</li><li>Now make the Jalfrezi  Add the onion, ginger, garlic and chili to a food processor and pulse until smooth.</li><li>Heat 2 tbsp of water in a deep sauce pan, add the onion mixture from step 4 along with all the Jalfrezi Spice Mix and cook for 3 minutes to release the flavours before adding in the green peppers, passata, peas and lemon juice, bring to the boil then reduce the heat to medium, cover the pan and cook for 20 minutes and just before serving stir through the coriander. Serve in a bowl with the koftas placed on top!</li></ol>", "aggregateLikes": 1, "dairyFree": true, "extendedIngredients": [{"aisle": "Ethnic Foods", "unitLong": "tablespoons", "amount": 2.0, "unitShort": "T", "metaInformation": [], "unit": "tbsp", "originalString": "2 tbsp Gram (chickpea) flour", "name": "besan gram flour"}, {"aisle": "Canned and Jar